<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,310,628,654]" box="[189,310,628,654]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,628,654]" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" reason="2">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,628,654]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1399,675,806]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
Thallus (bi)pinnate. Main axis of thallus 2.5–4.0 mm wide. Rhizoids present over the whole width of the ventral thallus surface. Female branches to 
<quantity box="[702,771,710,737]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long, archegonia in pairs, covered by a dense cluster of rhizoids with strongly thick-walled tips originating from beneath the apex of the female branch. Paraphyses lacking.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
